title: Biden administration names new Border Patrol chief
description: The Biden administration named Jason Owens as new chief of the Border Patrol. Owens's agents were heavily involved in the response to the massacre in Uvalde.

title: Minefields flooded by Ukraine dam breach pose new risk to civilians
description: Floods have obscured the location of land mines, according to deminers. Russia and Ukraine laid thousands of mines in the run-up to Ukraine's counteroffensive.

title: Boris Johnson resigns as member of U.K. Parliament over Partygate report
description: A committee had been investigating whether the former prime minister misled lawmakers about government gatherings that violated strict pandemic lockdown rules.

title: Iran seeks ‘billions’ worth of Russian aircraft and weapons in exchange for drones, U.S. says
description: White House expresses alarm over deepening military ties between Moscow and Tehran.

title: Greta Thunberg vows to keep up fight, moving on from school climate strikes
description: Thunberg, who has graduated from high school, became an icon of the youth climate movement after her first school strike in August 2018 outside Swedish parliament.

title: Ukraine presses counteroffensive as flood evacuations continue in south
description: Heavy fighting was reported in Zaporizhzhia and Donetsk regions but no major gains were claimed by Ukraine signaling the new phase of the war will be difficult.

title: An isolated crocodile laid eggs. She impregnated herself, scientists say.
description: A crocodile in a Costa Rican zoo impregnated herself asexually through facultative parthenogenesis to lay 14 eggs — the first known occurrence for the species.

title: India’s girl wrestlers watch in dismay as their heroes are crushed by police
description: The treatment of India's top female wrestlers protesting sexual harassment is discouraging to the girls pursuing the sport.

title: A Russia-Ukraine timeline: Key moments, from attack on Kyiv to counteroffensive
description: Here are some of the pivotal events in the course of the conflict, leading up to Ukraine's counterattack.

title: Sudan’s rapid decline into war evokes Somalia’s catastrophic collapse
description: Regional analysts warn of ominous parallels between Sudan and Somalia of 30 years ago.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Long-anticipated Ukraine counteroffensive is underway
description: Ukraine, armed with Western weapons, is stepping up its bid to retake land. Success in the southeastern Zaporizhzhia region could disrupt Russian supply lines.

title: The potent U.S. arsenal for Ukraine’s counteroffensive
description: The U.S. and Western allies have laid out a deliberate approach to arming Ukraine, focusing on systems that complement one another on the battlefield.
